olo 1120","1092":"1092","Egremont, Cumberland, England.":"Egremont, Cumberland, Anglie, United Kingdom","Bunbury, Nantwich, Cheshire, England.":"Bunbury, Cheshire, Anglie, United Kingdom","Bunbury, Cheshire, England":"Bunbury, Cheshire, Anglie"},"da":{"Abt 1089–1130":"omkring 1089–1130","1092–Female":"1092–Afdød","1120–Male":"1120–Afdød","1089–1130":"1089–1130","Abt 1089":"omkring 1089","1089":"1089","1120":"1120","1130":"1130","about 1120":"omkring 1120","1092":"1092","Egremont, Cumberland, England.":"Egremont, Cumbraland, England, United Kingdom","Bunbury, Nantwich, Cheshire, England.":"Bunbury, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","Bunbury, Cheshire, England":"Bunbury, Cheshire, England"},"nl":{"Abt 1089–1130":"circa 1089–1130","1092–Female":"1092–Overleden","1120–Male":"1120–Overleden","1089–1130":"1089–1130","Abt 1089":"circa 1089","1089":"1089","1120":"1120","1130":"1130","about 1120":"circa 1120","1092":"1092","Egremont, Cumberland, England.":"Egremont, Cumberland, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Bunbury, Nantwich, Cheshire, England.":"Bunbury, Cheshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Bunbury, Cheshire, England":"Bunbury, Cheshire, England"},"en":{"Abt 1089–1130":"about 1089–1130","1092–Female":"1092–Deceased","1120–Male":"1120–Deceased","1089–1130":"1089–1130","Abt 1089":"about 1089","1089":"1089","1120":"1120","1130":"1130","about 1120":"about 1120","1092":"1092","Egremont, Cumberland, England.":"Egremont, Cumberland, England, United Kingdom","Bunbury, Nantwich, Cheshire, England.":"Bunbury, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","Bunbury, Cheshire, England":"Bunbury, Cheshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"St.Pierre","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Normand, Armand, Lucien, Marcel, Andre, Emile, Cecile, Laurent, Michel, Alphonse, Antoine, Camille.","French (<b>Saint-Pierre</b>): habitational name from any of several places in various parts of France named Saint-Pierre (from the dedication of their churches to Saint Peter), or a nickname with the prefix <i>Saint</i> as an (ironic) attachment to the personal name or surname   Pierre  . Compare   Saintpierre  ,   St. Peter  .","Haitian (also <b>Saint-Pierre</b>): from <i>Saint-Pierre</i>, a nickname, ornamental name, or personal name composed of the French prefix <i>Saint</i> and the personal name   Pierre  , or perhaps a habitational name from a place in Haiti called Saint-Pierre (compare 1 above). Compare   Saintpierre  ."],"variants":[{"name":"St. Peter","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Alphy, Aurele, Celestine, Euclide, Henri, Lucien.","Americanized form of French <b>Saint-Pierre</b> (see   St. Pierre  )."]},{"name":"Pierre","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Jacques, Antoine, Yves, Michel, Jean Claude, Mireille, Jean Robert, Francois, Monique, Raoul, Serge.","French, Walloon, West Indian (mainly Haiti), and Mauritian:","from the personal name <i>Pierre</i>, French form of   Peter   (see also below). This is one of the most frequent surnames in Haiti (along with   Jean   and   Joseph  ) and in Saint Martin. It is also established elsewhere in the West Indies (e.g. in Trinidad and Tobago, Saint Lucia, Grenada, and Bahamas)."]},{"name":"Saintpierre","meanings":["French and Haitian: variant of <b>Saint-Pierre</b> (see   St. Pierre  ) and, in North America, (also) an altered form of this. This form of the surname is more common in Haiti than in France."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Baron William St.Pierre was born about 1089, in Bunbury, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son with Mrs William de St Pierre. He died in 1130, in Egremont, Cumberland, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 42."},"et":{"Abt 1089–1130":"umbes 1089–1130","1092–Female":"1092–Surnud","1120–Male":"1120–Surnud","1089–1130":"1089–1130","Abt 1089":"umbes 1089","1089":"1089","1120":"1120","1130":"1130","about 1120":"umbes 1120","1092":"1092","Egremont, Cumberland, England.":"Egremont, Cumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bunbury, Nantwich, Cheshire, England.":"Bunbury, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bunbury, Cheshire, England":"Bunbury, Cheshire, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1089–1130":"noin 1089–1130","1092–Female":"1092–Kuollut","1120–Male":"1120–Kuollut","1089–1130":"1089–1130","Abt 1089":"noin 1089","1089":"1089","1120":"1120","1130":"1130","about 1120":"noin 1120","1092":"1092","Egremont, Cumberland, England.":"Egremont, Cumberland, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Bunbury, Nantwich, Cheshire, England.":"Bunbury, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Bunbury, Cheshire, England":"Bunbury, Cheshire, England"},"fr":{"Abt 1089–1130":"environ 1089–1130","1092–Female":"1092–Décédée","1120–Male":"1120–Décédé","1089–1130":"1089–1130","Abt 1089":"environ 1089","1089":"1089","1120":"1120","1130":"1130","about 1120":"environ 1120","1092":"1092","Egremont, Cumberland, England.":"Egremont, Cumberland, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Bunbury, Nantwich, Cheshire, England.":"Bunbury, Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Bunbury, Cheshire, England":"Bunbury, Cheshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Baron William St.Pierre est né environ 1089, à Bunbury